This directory is where documentation of the project will be generated.
Doxygen is used to create documentation for FIRE.
Doxygen config file resides in this directory, "FIRE6/documentation"

As the documentation will be changed frequently in upcoming commits,
the results of compilation won't be included in repo for the time being.

Documentation is generated without caller\callee graph for now.

To generate docs you need to have doxygen installed.

To generate docs run in FIRE6 directory:
* make doc

This will create html/ and latex/ subfolders here.
html/ contains complete docs, latex/ contains latex sources.

To generate .pdf from latex sources, run in FIRE6 directory:
* make doc_pdf
You will need to have appropriate tools installed, like pdflatex
This will generate refman.pdf and place it directly in documentation/

To view docs after creation, either
* open FIRE6/documentation/html/index.html in your Web Browser
* open FIRE6/documentation/refman.pdf (after generating it)

To delete documentation run
* make cleandoc
